{"key":"processedPost-14837534","value":{"id":14837534,"first":14821310,"last":14837809,"when":1311860673,"utime":"07/28/11 04:44 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />If you look it up they are called WIDE MOUTH jars. I don't care if the lid is the same as a regular quart jar lid it has a wide mouth in comparison to the rest of the jar.... <br /></blockquote><br /><br />That is the wrong type of jar, and whether the lid is wider than the rest of the jar is irrelevant.&nbsp; We use the short, squat wide-mouth half pints because they're wider than they are tall, so the substrate doesn't pack and/or get oxygen starved at the bottom.&nbsp; The tall, skinny half pints are vastly inferior, based on tens of thousands of independent grows.<br />RR","title":"Re: Super Fine Verm."}}